text: Enjoy the day and week. Back on Monday. Invest and trade well!

I dont and never have understood the Bears v. Bulls argument. Mr. Market doesnt think in those terms. Its "us" v. Mr. Market. The biggest problem most of us have with trading/investing is ourselves. Our fears, dogmas, unwillingness to do homework and greed.
As Pogo said, "we have met the enemy and he is us."

We maybe entering an earnings recession, yet bullish talking heads are discussing misses that are better than expectations I am mindful of Monty Python's Upper Class Twit of the Year - contestants Nigel Incubator Jones who's best friend is a tree and in the spare time he

Group stink is always visible this early in the morning. Think not first level, but second level. And avoid the crowds, mostly. Invest using a calculator and a contrarian streak. Keep your children and portfolios away from the self confident. And do your homework. Enjoy the day

Today we will hear why $AAPL is cheap (at $164) from the same talking heads who thought $AAPL was cheap (at $230) last August. As I tweeted "investment wisdom is always 20/20 when seen through the rear view mirror." @SquawkCNBC @andrewrsorkin @beckyquick @tomkeene @lizclaman
